Independent research work. The thesis is written in accordance with the requirements and guidelines  and is defended at public disputation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the master's thesis is to obtain in-depth knowledge and skills of a narrower field of speciality and acquire experience in independent research together with skills in compiling a research manuscript.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has successfully defended a master's thesis: 1. has in-depth knowledge of a narrower field of the specialty 2. can formulate the main positions of the field of specialty 3. can critically analyse the positions published in the specialty literature both in his or her own language and in a foreign language 4. can present his or her positions, conclusions and generalisations and argumentatively justify them 6. can examine and analyse empirical data 7. can defend his or her views and presented theses and critically assess them 8. can apply different research methods 9. is aware of the requirements applicable to research
